Second Lady Karen Pence and Dr. Elinore F. McCance-Katz visited the Baltimore Crisis Response, Inc. (BCRI) to learn about the mental health, substance use, and suicide prevention services offered. They toured the facility and met with staff members and patients. BCRI is one of six National Suicide Prevention Lifelines in Maryland and provides community education and training programs. Patients shared their recovery stories, highlighting the impact BCRI had on their lives. Mrs. Pence emphasized the importance of addressing mental health issues and thanked the staff for their work in providing care and services. BCRI provides crisis services to Baltimore residents through mobile and residential treatment services. PREVENTS, a national health campaign aimed at preventing suicide, was also mentioned.